choices.text:
I am not a prime number.
I am between 20 and 40.
I am one more than a square number.
What number am I?
The number is 31, as it satisfies all three conditions given in the riddle. 

- It is not a prime number, so it must be a composite number.
- It is between 20 and 40, as you have specified.
- A square number plus one is always one more than that square number, and the only square number between 20 and 40 is 25 (which is 5 squared). So by being one more than a square number, this number must be 31 (which is 5 plus 1).

Therefore, the number in question is 31.
